{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I want us to start\nby thinking about this device,"},{"time":4110,"text":"the phone that's very likely\nin your pockets right now."},{"time":7743,"text":"Over 40 percent of Americans \ncheck their phones"},{"time":10884,"text":"within five minutes\nof waking up every morning."},{"time":14138,"text":"And then they look at it\nanother 50 times during the day."},{"time":17887,"text":"Grownups consider this device\nto be a necessity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22890,"text":"But now I want you to imagine it\nin the hands of a three-year-old,"},{"time":27840,"text":"and as a society, we get anxious."},{"time":31114,"text":"Parents are very worried"},{"time":32366,"text":"that this device is going to stunt\ntheir children's social growth;"},{"time":35870,"text":"that it's going to keep them\nfrom getting up and moving;"},{"time":38559,"text":"that somehow,"},{"time":39955,"text":"this is going to disrupt childhood."},{"time":44282,"text":"So, I want to challenge this attitude."},{"time":48404,"text":"I can envision a future"},{"time":50499,"text":"where we would be excited to see\na preschooler interacting with a screen."},{"time":56527,"text":"These screens can get kids\nup and moving even more."},{"time":62089,"text":"They have the power to tell us more\nabout what a child is learning"},{"time":65268,"text":"than a standardized test can."},{"time":67139,"text":"And here's the really crazy thought:"},{"time":69119,"text":"I believe that these screens\nhave the power"},{"time":71952,"text":"to prompt more real-life conversations"},{"time":74685,"text":"between kids and their parents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78482,"text":"Now, I was perhaps\nan unlikely champion for this cause."},{"time":81792,"text":"I studied children's literature"},{"time":83777,"text":"because I was going to work\nwith kids and books."},{"time":86834,"text":"But about 20 years ago,"},{"time":88959,"text":"I had an experience that shifted my focus."},{"time":92968,"text":"I was helping lead a research study\nabout preschoolers and websites."},{"time":97190,"text":"And I walked in and was assigned\na three-year-old named Maria."},{"time":100973,"text":"Maria had actually never seen\na computer before."},{"time":104892,"text":"So the first thing I had to do\nwas teach her how to use the mouse,"},{"time":108062,"text":"and when I opened up the screen,\nshe moved it across the screen,"},{"time":113516,"text":"and she stopped on a character\nnamed X the Owl."},{"time":117283,"text":"And when she did that,"},{"time":118553,"text":"the owl lifted his wing and waved at her."},{"time":122369,"text":"Maria dropped the mouse,\npushed back from the table, leaped up"},{"time":125766,"text":"and started waving\nfrantically back at him."},{"time":129994,"text":"Her connection to that character"},{"time":132270,"text":"was visceral."},{"time":133564,"text":"This wasn't a passive screen experience."},{"time":137128,"text":"This was a human experience."},{"time":140356,"text":"And it was exactly appropriate\nfor a three-year-old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"I've now worked at PBS Kids\nfor more than 15 years,"},{"time":148999,"text":"and my work there is focused on\nharnessing the power of technology"},{"time":153644,"text":"as a positive in children's lives."},{"time":156330,"text":"I believe that as a society,\nwe're missing a big opportunity."},{"time":159816,"text":"We're letting our fear and our skepticism"},{"time":162083,"text":"about these devices"},{"time":163540,"text":"hold us back from realizing\ntheir potential"},{"time":166076,"text":"in our children's lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168670,"text":"Fear about kids and technology\nis nothing new;"},{"time":171910,"text":"we've been here before."},{"time":173568,"text":"Over 50 years ago, the debate was raging\nabout the newly dominant media:"},{"time":178309,"text":"the television."},{"time":180008,"text":"That box in the living room?"},{"time":182032,"text":"It might be separating kids\nfrom one another."},{"time":184702,"text":"It might keep them away\nfrom the outside world."},{"time":188524,"text":"But this is the moment when Fred Rogers,"},{"time":191590,"text":"the long-running host\nof \"Mister Rogers' Neighborhood,\""},{"time":194697,"text":"challenged society\nto look at television as a tool,"},{"time":199451,"text":"a tool that could promote\nemotional growth."},{"time":202194,"text":"Here's what he did:"},{"time":203401,"text":"he looked out from the screen,\nand he held a conversation,"},{"time":207797,"text":"as if he were speaking\nto each child individually"},{"time":212067,"text":"about feelings."},{"time":213833,"text":"And then he would pause"},{"time":216063,"text":"and let them think about them."},{"time":219271,"text":"You can see his influence\nacross the media landscape today,"},{"time":222963,"text":"but at the time, this was revolutionary."},{"time":226521,"text":"He shifted the way we looked at television\nin the lives of children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233103,"text":"Today it's not just one box."},{"time":235774,"text":"Kids are surrounded by devices."},{"time":238317,"text":"And I'm also a parent -- I understand\nthis feeling of anxiety."},{"time":243949,"text":"But I want us to look\nat three common fears"},{"time":247109,"text":"that parents have,"},{"time":248646,"text":"and see if we can shift our focus"},{"time":251514,"text":"to the opportunity that's in each of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254871,"text":"So."},{"time":256048,"text":"Fear number one:"},{"time":257950,"text":"\"Screens are passive."},{"time":259632,"text":"This is going to keep our kids\nfrom getting up and moving.\""},{"time":263905,"text":"Chris Kratt and Martin Kratt\nare zoologist brothers"},{"time":267432,"text":"who host a show about animals\ncalled \"Wild Kratts.\""},{"time":270887,"text":"And they approached the PBS team to say,"},{"time":273274,"text":"\"Can we do something with those cameras"},{"time":275461,"text":"that are built into every device now?"},{"time":277786,"text":"Could those cameras capture\na very natural kid play pattern --"},{"time":282495,"text":"pretending to be animals?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":285264,"text":"So we started with bats."},{"time":288541,"text":"And when kids came in to play this game,"},{"time":290707,"text":"they loved seeing themselves\non-screen with wings."},{"time":294246,"text":"But my favorite part of this,"},{"time":295913,"text":"when the game was over\nand we turned off the screens?"},{"time":299229,"text":"The kids kept being bats."},{"time":301166,"text":"They kept flying around the room,"},{"time":303127,"text":"they kept veering left and right\nto catch mosquitoes."},{"time":306736,"text":"And they remembered things."},{"time":309171,"text":"They remembered that bats fly at night."},{"time":312601,"text":"And they remembered that when bats sleep,"},{"time":314953,"text":"they hang upside down\nand fold their wings in."},{"time":318621,"text":"This game definitely got kids\nup and moving."},{"time":321849,"text":"But also, now when kids go outside,"},{"time":325063,"text":"do they look at a bird and think,"},{"time":327284,"text":"\"How does a bird fly\ndifferently than I flew"},{"time":330048,"text":"when I was a bat?\""},{"time":332627,"text":"The digital technology prompted\nembodied learning"},{"time":335954,"text":"that kids can now take out into the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340361,"text":"Fear number two:"},{"time":343927,"text":"\"Playing games on these screens\nis just a waste of time."},{"time":347023,"text":"It's going to distract children\nfrom their education.\""},{"time":352007,"text":"Game developers know"},{"time":353432,"text":"that you can learn a lot\nabout a player's skill"},{"time":355866,"text":"by looking at the back-end data:"},{"time":357968,"text":"Where did a player pause?"},{"time":360306,"text":"Where did they make a few mistakes\nbefore they found the right answer?"},{"time":363976,"text":"My team wanted to take that tool set\nand apply it to academic learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369414,"text":"Our producer in Boston, WGBH,"},{"time":372439,"text":"created a series of Curious George games"},{"time":375186,"text":"focused on math."},{"time":377608,"text":"And researchers came in and had\n80 preschoolers play these games."},{"time":383415,"text":"They then gave all 80\nof those preschoolers"},{"time":386003,"text":"a standardized math test."},{"time":388613,"text":"We could see early on"},{"time":389808,"text":"that these games\nwere actually helping kids"},{"time":391960,"text":"understand some key skills."},{"time":394388,"text":"But our partners at UCLA\nwanted us to dig deeper."},{"time":398344,"text":"They focus on data analysis\nand student assessment."},{"time":402399,"text":"And they wanted to take\nthat back-end game-play data"},{"time":405871,"text":"and see if they could use it\nto predict a child's math scores."},{"time":410068,"text":"So they made a neural net --\nthey essentially trained the computer"},{"time":413742,"text":"to use this data,"},{"time":415288,"text":"and here are the results."},{"time":416812,"text":"This is a subset of the children's\nstandardized math scores."},{"time":421424,"text":"And this"},{"time":423459,"text":"is the computer's prediction\nof each child's score,"},{"time":427140,"text":"based on playing\nsome Curious George games."},{"time":431688,"text":"The prediction is astonishingly accurate,"},{"time":434122,"text":"especially considering the fact\nthat these games weren't built"},{"time":437158,"text":"for assessment."},{"time":438901,"text":"The team that did this study\nbelieves that games like these"},{"time":441893,"text":"can teach us more\nabout a child's cognitive learning"},{"time":445602,"text":"than a standardized test can."},{"time":448800,"text":"What if games could reduce\ntesting time in the classroom?"},{"time":452999,"text":"What if they could reduce testing anxiety?"},{"time":456600,"text":"How could they give teachers\nsnapshots of insight"},{"time":460049,"text":"to help them better focus\ntheir individualized learning?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":466147,"text":"So the third fear I want to address"},{"time":469076,"text":"is the one that I think\nis often the biggest."},{"time":472084,"text":"And that's this:"},{"time":474091,"text":"\"These screens are isolating me\nfrom my child.\""},{"time":479011,"text":"Let's play out a scenario."},{"time":481146,"text":"Let's say that you are a parent,"},{"time":483883,"text":"and you need 25 minutes\nof uninterrupted time"},{"time":486905,"text":"to get dinner ready."},{"time":488487,"text":"And in order to do that,\nyou hand a tablet to your three-year-old."},{"time":492170,"text":"Now, this is a moment\nwhere you probably feel very guilty"},{"time":495171,"text":"about what you just did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497745,"text":"But now imagine this:"},{"time":499769,"text":"Twenty minutes later,\nyou receive a text message."},{"time":502843,"text":"on that cell phone\nthat's always within arm's reach."},{"time":505841,"text":"And it says: \"Alex just matched\nfive rhyming words."},{"time":510403,"text":"Ask him to play this game with you."},{"time":512270,"text":"Can you think of a word\nthat rhymes with 'cat'?"},{"time":515943,"text":"Or how about 'ball'?\""},{"time":518797,"text":"In our studies, when parents receive\nsimple tips like these,"},{"time":522548,"text":"they felt empowered."},{"time":524217,"text":"They were so excited"},{"time":525851,"text":"to play these games\nat the dinner table with their kids."},{"time":528499,"text":"And the kids loved it, too."},{"time":530125,"text":"Not only did it feel like magic\nthat their parents knew"},{"time":533064,"text":"what they had been playing,"},{"time":534651,"text":"kids love to play games\nwith their parents."},{"time":539176,"text":"Just the act of talking to kids\nabout their media"},{"time":543131,"text":"can be incredibly powerful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545829,"text":"Last summer, Texas Tech University\npublished a study"},{"time":549178,"text":"that the show \"Daniel Tiger's\nNeighborhood\" could promote"},{"time":552564,"text":"the development of empathy among children."},{"time":555980,"text":"But there was a really important\ncatch to this study:"},{"time":558803,"text":"the greatest benefit was only\nwhen parents talked to kids"},{"time":563284,"text":"about what they watched."},{"time":565194,"text":"Neither just watching"},{"time":567218,"text":"nor just talking about it was enough;"},{"time":569242,"text":"it was the combination that was key."},{"time":573214,"text":"So when I read this study,"},{"time":574691,"text":"I started thinking about"},{"time":576119,"text":"how rarely parents of preschoolers\nactually talk to kids about the content"},{"time":581396,"text":"of what they're playing\nand what they're watching."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583806,"text":"And so I decided to try it\nwith my four-year-old."},{"time":586293,"text":"I said,"},{"time":588077,"text":"\"Were you playing a car game\nearlier today?\""},{"time":591352,"text":"And Benjamin perked up and said,"},{"time":593358,"text":"\"Yes! And did you see\nthat I made my car out of a pickle?"},{"time":597227,"text":"It was really hard to open the trunk.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":599338,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601020,"text":"This hilarious conversation\nabout what was fun in the game"},{"time":605129,"text":"and what could have been better"},{"time":606664,"text":"continued all the way\nto school that morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612340,"text":"I'm not here to suggest to you\nthat all digital media is great for kids."},{"time":617939,"text":"There are legitimate reasons\nfor us to be concerned"},{"time":620649,"text":"about the current state\nof children's content"},{"time":623132,"text":"on these screens."},{"time":625062,"text":"And it's right for us\nto be thinking about balance:"},{"time":627861,"text":"Where do screens fit\nagainst all the other things"},{"time":631545,"text":"that a child needs to do\nto learn and to grow?"},{"time":636258,"text":"But when we fixate on our fears about it,"},{"time":639089,"text":"we forget a really major point,"},{"time":641897,"text":"and that is, that kids are living\nin the same world that we live in,"},{"time":646119,"text":"the world where the grownups\ncheck their phones"},{"time":648828,"text":"more than 50 times a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651886,"text":"Screens are a part of children's lives."},{"time":656048,"text":"And if we pretend that they aren't,"},{"time":659072,"text":"or if we get overwhelmed by our fear,"},{"time":662091,"text":"kids are never going to learn\nhow and why to use them."},{"time":667905,"text":"What if we start raising our expectations"},{"time":671194,"text":"for this media?"},{"time":673125,"text":"What if we start talking to kids regularly"},{"time":675422,"text":"about the content on these screens?"},{"time":678091,"text":"What if we start looking\nfor the positive impacts"},{"time":681674,"text":"that this technology can have\nin our children's lives?"},{"time":686222,"text":"That's when the potential of these tools\ncan become a reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691344,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692563,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}